The Telegraph - Calcutta
 Monday, June 30, 2003  Good Morning Hello It's Monday, June 30, 2003				 																Roads to avoid				 																																	Lower Circular Road, between Camac Street and Lansdowne Road, due to work on the AJC Bose Road flyover. Buses and minibuses heading towards Alipore zoo will take the Lansdowne Road-Elgin Road-Ashutosh Mukherjee Road-Chowringhee-Queensway-Hospital Road-Lower Circular Road route. Those travelling towards Beckbagan will take the Ashutosh Mukherjee Road-Hazra Road-Ballygunge Phari-Syed Amir Ali Avenue route.				 																Book				 																																	The Pleasure of a Woman by Janet Fine will be launched, as part of the Reading Kamasutra event, at Oxford Bookstore at 7 pm. A discussion with the author, Moon Moon Sen and others will follow.				 																Workshop				 																																	Rupa Ganguly will attend The Workshop organised by Sanlaap at 6A, Deshapriya Park East, 11 am. An exhibition will be held of embroidered garments and handicrafts. 				 																Tagore				 																																	A reading of Rabindranath Tagores poetry, organised by Tagore Research Institute, at Rabindracharcha Bhavan, Kalighat Park, from 6.30 pm.				 																Audio play				 																																	A series of audio plays based on Rabindranath Tagores works, presented by Unmesh, at Bangla Akademi from 6.30 pm.				 																On stage				 																																	Natadha will stage Mahabharata at Academy of Fine Arts at 6.30 pm.
